---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="MB vs GB: Data Storage Units Explained Simply" description="Understand the difference between megabytes and gigabytes with real-world examples. Learn how much data common files use and what storage sizes mean." keywords="MB vs GB, megabyte gigabyte, data storage units, how much is a GB, file sizes explained, storage conversion, data units">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Data</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">MB vs GB: Data Storage Units Explained Simply</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 2, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Phones advertise storage in GB, photos take up MB, and apps measure in both. If the relationship between these units confuses you, here is a clear, jargon-free explanation with real-world examples.</p>

      <h2>The Scale</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 GB = 1,000 MB (decimal) or 1,024 MB (binary)</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">1 MB = 1,000 KB | 1 KB = 1,000 bytes</p>
      </div>

      <h2>The Full Hierarchy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Byte:</strong> A single character of text</li>
        <li><strong>Kilobyte (KB):</strong> 1,000 bytes — a short email</li>
        <li><strong>Megabyte (MB):</strong> 1,000 KB — a high-res photo</li>
        <li><strong>Gigabyte (GB):</strong> 1,000 MB — about 250 songs</li>
        <li><strong>Terabyte (TB):</strong> 1,000 GB — a large hard drive</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Real-World File Sizes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Text email:</strong> 10-50 KB</li>
        <li><strong>Smartphone photo:</strong> 3-8 MB</li>
        <li><strong>DSLR RAW photo:</strong> 25-60 MB</li>
        <li><strong>MP3 song (4 min):</strong> 4-8 MB</li>
        <li><strong>Netflix movie (SD):</strong> 1-2 GB</li>
        <li><strong>Netflix movie (HD):</strong> 3-5 GB</li>
        <li><strong>Netflix movie (4K):</strong> 7-14 GB</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile app:</strong> 50-500 MB</li>
        <li><strong>PC video game:</strong> 30-150 GB</li>
        <li><strong>1 hour of Zoom:</strong> 500 MB-1.5 GB</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Much Can You Store?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>32 GB phone:</strong> About 7,000 photos or 8,000 songs</li>
        <li><strong>128 GB phone:</strong> About 30,000 photos or 32,000 songs</li>
        <li><strong>256 GB laptop:</strong> About 50 HD movies or 60,000 songs</li>
        <li><strong>1 TB hard drive:</strong> About 200 HD movies or 250,000 photos</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Plans and Streaming</h2>
      <p>Mobile data plans are measured in GB. Here is how far common plans stretch:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>1 GB/month:</strong> Light email and browsing, minimal video</li>
        <li><strong>5 GB/month:</strong> Moderate browsing, social media, some music streaming</li>
        <li><strong>15 GB/month:</strong> Regular streaming, video calls, moderate Netflix</li>
        <li><strong>Unlimited:</strong> Heavy 4K streaming, large downloads, hotspot use</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Understanding these units helps you choose the right phone, plan, or cloud storage tier without overpaying for capacity you do not need.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/data" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Data Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/data" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
